    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>We used the dried tube specimen (DTS) procedure to develop the COVID-19 Serology Control Panel (CSCP). The CSCP contains five well-characterized SARS-CoV-2 pooled plasma samples made available for labs around the world to compare test kits, use for external quality assurance, harmonize laboratory testing, and train laboratory workers.</jats:p>\n                <jats:sec>\n                  <jats:title>Article Summary Line</jats:title>\n                  <jats:p>The dried tube specimen system is a highly effective and resilient way to provide laboratories with well-characterized serology materials. The CSCP can help clinical laboratories inform their choice of diagnostic test to supplement clinical diagnoses of SARS-CoV-2 infection.</jats:p>\n                </jats:sec>",
